I've created the React settings components for user management in `web/dashboard/src/features/settings/`. Here's what was implemented:

**Created files:**

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `Settings.tsx` | Main settings page with tab navigation (Profile, Security, Organization) |
| `ProfileSettings.tsx` | User profile editing form with validation for name/email |
| `SecuritySettings.tsx` | Password change form with strength validation and 2FA toggle with verification modal |
| `OrganizationSettings.tsx` | Organization info editing and team member management (invite, role change, remove) |
| `types.ts` | TypeScript types for User, Organization, forms, and validation |
| `api.ts` | API calls to auth-service endpoints (`PUT /api/user/profile`, `PUT /api/user/password`, etc.) |
| `Toast.tsx` & `useToast.ts` | Toast notification system for success/error feedback |
| `index.ts` | Barrel exports for clean imports |

**Features:**
- Form validation with real-time error messages
- Password strength requirements (8+ chars, uppercase, lowercase, number)
- Toast notifications for save feedback
- Role-based member management (owner/admin only)
- 2FA enable/disable with QR code modal flow
- Dark mode support
- Responsive design

**Type-check:** ✅ Passed (`npm run type-check`)

